1
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:43,840
=No Pain No Gain=
(Adapted from the Qidian novel)

2
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:47,180
("Losing Money to Be a Tycoon"
by Qingshan Quzui)

3
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:50,220
=Episode 17=
(This story is purely fictional)

4
00:01:51,940 --> 00:01:52,740
Designated driver?

5
00:01:53,260 --> 00:01:53,940
What's going on?

6
00:01:55,820 --> 00:01:57,740
What is this, Huang?

7
00:01:57,857 --> 00:01:59,635
Are you sure
you called the right number?

8
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:02,820
I'm 100% sure.

9
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,380
He is working as a designated driver.

10
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:07,460
He has changed completely,

11
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:10,020
but I'm sure
he is planning something big.

12
00:02:11,380 --> 00:02:12,502
What big thing is he planning

13
00:02:12,524 --> 00:02:14,540
that requires him
to work as a designated driver?

14
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,260
Trying to understand Mr. Pei

15
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:27,380
is getting more and more difficult.

16
00:02:50,660 --> 00:02:52,140
Designated Driver, P?

17
00:02:52,260 --> 00:02:53,100
Lin Wan.

18
00:02:53,435 --> 00:02:55,946
Huang and the rest told me
you are working as a designated driver.

19
00:02:55,968 --> 00:02:56,780
I didn't believe them.

20
00:02:57,013 --> 00:02:58,780
Are you really working
as a designated driver?

21
00:02:59,260 --> 00:03:00,420
Sorry, Lin Wan.

22
00:03:00,420 --> 00:03:01,500
They are recording.

23
00:03:01,500 --> 00:03:02,780
I must finish my greeting.

24
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:04,220
Hello. CC Designated Driver

25
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:05,060
is happy to serve you.

26
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:06,940
I've arrived
at the agreed pickup point on time.

27
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:08,420
All right.

28
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:10,860
Mr. Pei,

29
00:03:11,940 --> 00:03:13,700
what are you trying to do?

30
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:18,220
Of course, I'm experiencing life.

31
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:19,980
Otherwise, do you think I lack money?

32
00:03:43,057 --> 00:03:45,413
Professional designated driver
lets you arrive home safely.

33
00:03:45,435 --> 00:03:46,860
Protecting you is our duty.

34
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,540
You have arrived at your destination.

35
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:52,060
Mr. Pei.

36
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:54,660
Take a walk with me.

37
00:03:57,660 --> 00:03:58,900
The people of the company

38
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,140
think you are planning something big

39
00:04:01,140 --> 00:04:02,820
by working as a designated driver.

40
00:04:03,220 --> 00:04:04,140
Are you

41
00:04:04,140 --> 00:04:06,020
going to venture into another industry?

42
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:09,020
All of you are overcomplicating things.

43
00:04:10,820 --> 00:04:11,660
Forget it.

44
00:04:11,780 --> 00:04:13,220
You are so mysterious.

45
00:04:13,220 --> 00:04:14,857
I won't ask
if you don't feel like telling.

46
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:16,860
I'm not.

47
00:04:16,924 --> 00:04:18,346
You work as a designated driver

48
00:04:18,346 --> 00:04:20,020
but I can't even find you
at your office.

49
00:04:20,660 --> 00:04:22,500
Didn't I tell you before?

50
00:04:22,660 --> 00:04:23,940
When it comes to work,

51
00:04:23,940 --> 00:04:25,700
you can decide everything yourself.

52
00:04:27,540 --> 00:04:28,100
I...

53
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:35,940
Tell me.

54
00:04:37,857 --> 00:04:40,340
After the Divine Mountains and Seas
began its development,

55
00:04:40,340 --> 00:04:41,940
everything has been going smoothly.

56
00:04:42,620 --> 00:04:44,420
I have a feeling

57
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:46,060
that its content is lacking something,

58
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:47,740
but I can't really point out what it is.

59
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,300
If that's your question,

60
00:04:50,990 --> 00:04:53,500
it might be a problem
with the theme and core content.

61
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:57,500
You previously said

62
00:04:57,860 --> 00:04:59,280
innovation in games

63
00:04:59,280 --> 00:05:01,740
should have relevance to the times
and intellectual depth.

64
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:02,820
I learned from that.

65
00:05:05,060 --> 00:05:06,940
Did I say something like that before?

66
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:10,420
I think

67
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:11,500
you can think about

68
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:13,220
why you develop games.

69
00:05:14,260 --> 00:05:15,980
Because I really like games.

70
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:17,100
I want to develop a game

71
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:19,660
that many people like.

72
00:05:21,340 --> 00:05:22,500
Have you thought about

73
00:05:22,980 --> 00:05:24,620
why you like games

74
00:05:25,060 --> 00:05:26,500
and why other people like them?

75
00:05:29,220 --> 00:05:31,300
Reality is too harsh.

76
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:33,620
I want a shelter,

77
00:05:33,860 --> 00:05:34,900
a Utopia perhaps.

78
00:05:38,060 --> 00:05:39,060
Yes.

79
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:40,980
Life always

80
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:43,180
feels suffocating.

81
00:05:43,980 --> 00:05:44,860
You can't

82
00:05:44,860 --> 00:05:45,860
really escape from it.

83
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:48,420
However, we can take a nap

84
00:05:48,420 --> 00:05:49,460
and have a nice dream.

85
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:54,100
If you want
to resonate with more people,

86
00:05:54,340 --> 00:05:56,540
you must first resonate with yourself.

87
00:05:57,980 --> 00:05:59,380
Data, gameplay, and style

88
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:01,180
can all be replicated.

89
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,740
Only emotions

90
00:06:02,980 --> 00:06:04,340
cannot be replicated.

91
00:06:19,835 --> 00:06:21,020
You are a person with ideals

92
00:06:21,260 --> 00:06:22,380
and emotions.

93
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:24,140
I believe you can surely do it.

94
00:06:43,635 --> 00:06:45,180
When I have questions in the future,

95
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,140
can I get you as my designated driver?

96
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:48,900
Can I?

97
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:53,580
Whatever.

98
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:07,820
I have a new order.

99
00:07:08,260 --> 00:07:09,260
I have to leave.

100
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:11,020
Go ahead.

101
00:07:11,146 --> 00:07:12,140
I need to leave, as well.

102
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:17,820
My electric scooter
is still in your car.

103
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,500
Let's go retrieve it now.

104
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:23,700
Are you in a rush?

105
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:25,820
Not really.

106
00:07:26,460 --> 00:07:27,700
You walk quickly.

107
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:29,500
I'll slow down.

108
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:40,380
Here you go.

109
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:44,820
I'm leaving. Bye.

110
00:07:44,820 --> 00:07:45,940
Ride safe.

111
00:07:52,580 --> 00:07:53,140
Hello.

112
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:54,380
Bao. Lv.

113
00:07:54,613 --> 00:07:57,000
You don't have to worry about
not being able to contact Mr. Pei.

114
00:07:57,102 --> 00:07:58,820
Isn't he working
as a designated driver now?

115
00:07:58,820 --> 00:08:00,060
Besides using a platform,

116
00:08:00,060 --> 00:08:01,700
he is also
working part-time at an offline

117
00:08:01,700 --> 00:08:02,730
designated driver company.

118
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:04,940
I spoke to the company

119
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:05,940
to hire him for a month.

120
00:08:05,940 --> 00:08:07,500
When he drives in the future,

121
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:08,902
we can discuss the project with him.

122
00:08:08,924 --> 00:08:10,140
Lin Wan, you're amazing.

123
00:08:10,140 --> 00:08:11,420
You're really smart.

124
00:08:16,540 --> 00:08:19,180
(Shenhua International)

125
00:08:19,180 --> 00:08:20,740
(Zhongdian Web Fiction)

126
00:08:20,740 --> 00:08:21,300
Mr. Pei,

127
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:22,940
the script is almost ready.

128
00:08:22,940 --> 00:08:25,300
The hard copy has been sent to Shi Huo
and the other actors.

129
00:08:25,391 --> 00:08:27,720
The director is getting his crew
and preparing everything.

130
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,180
The crew shirts are also ready.

131
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:31,580
Mr. Pei, you must attend
the pre-shoot ceremony.

132
00:08:31,580 --> 00:08:32,740
Sure. Okay. No problem.

133
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:33,924
Okay. I'm hanging up.

134
00:08:39,940 --> 00:08:41,340
This is serious.

135
00:08:41,340 --> 00:08:42,260
It's over for him now.

136
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:43,060
This is over.

137
00:08:44,940 --> 00:08:46,180
What are you talking about?

138
00:08:46,324 --> 00:08:47,220
Huang, take a look.

139
00:08:47,220 --> 00:08:48,860
Lu Zhiyao is trending again.

140
00:08:49,191 --> 00:08:50,780
Isn't it normal for him to be trending?

141
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:51,420
It's different.

142
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:52,980
This time, it's different.

143
00:08:52,980 --> 00:08:54,180
Come and take a look.

144
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:01,340
(Do you know who I met today?)

145
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:03,260
(Idol-chasing Diary)
(Isn't this your idol, Lu Zhiyao?)

146
00:09:03,260 --> 00:09:05,190
(Lu Zhiyao putting up airs)
(Mr. Lu is still as popular.)

147
00:09:05,191 --> 00:09:06,480
(His expression is still cold.)

148
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,460
(I helped you fans ask around,
and I heard Mr. Lu)

149
00:09:08,460 --> 00:09:10,060
(has accepted
a famous director's movie.)

150
00:09:10,060 --> 00:09:11,319
(He might even be more popular now.)

151
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,899
(Looking at his new style,
Mr. Lu is probably switching genres)

152
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:15,550
(and starting to
do some serious acting.)

153
00:09:16,020 --> 00:09:17,140
(It's actually a wig?)

154
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:19,100
(Mr. Lu is still behaving like an idol.)

155
00:09:19,940 --> 00:09:21,660
(What news is Mr. Lu reading?)

156
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:22,940
(Why is he frowning?)

157
00:09:25,580 --> 00:09:28,140
(Why did he splash all the coffee
his assistant brought him?)

158
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:28,740
(Perhaps)

159
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:30,300
(he is still immersed in his role.)

160
00:09:30,435 --> 00:09:31,980
(When Mr. Lu realized I was filming,)

161
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:33,860
(he showed his iconic smile again.)

162
00:09:34,220 --> 00:09:35,340
(He is domineering indeed.)

163
00:09:35,368 --> 00:09:36,260
(I'll be going now.)

164
00:09:37,613 --> 00:09:39,680
His expression changed
as soon as he saw the fan.

165
00:09:39,813 --> 00:09:41,324
He's forcefully changing his style now.

166
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:43,260
The new film was roasted by fans

167
00:09:43,260 --> 00:09:44,380
to be a box office bomb.

168
00:09:44,391 --> 00:09:45,849
They even made this into stickers.

169
00:09:45,850 --> 00:09:48,368
Lu Zhiyao is so angry that
he closed his social media accounts.

170
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,780
Send me these stickers.
I'll save and use them.

171
00:09:50,780 --> 00:09:52,560
Sure. No problem.
I'll share it in the group.

172
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:55,180
Someone revealed
that after he closed his accounts,

173
00:09:55,180 --> 00:09:56,940
he was still acting the same
and not improving.

174
00:09:56,940 --> 00:09:58,380
He continued to act all high and mighty

175
00:09:58,380 --> 00:09:59,260
at the production set.

176
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:00,620
In the end, he was replaced.

177
00:10:01,580 --> 00:10:03,420
He was doing a film
with a famous director.

178
00:10:03,420 --> 00:10:04,591
Moreover, he is the male lead.

179
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:06,820
He'll be so frustrated
after losing this gig.

180
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:08,420
Doesn't it feel great?

181
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:09,620
Yes.

182
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:16,620
(Mandy, Lu Zhiyao's Manager)

183
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:32,820
Sibo,

184
00:10:33,180 --> 00:10:34,220
it's like this.

185
00:10:34,540 --> 00:10:36,380
Yao is unhappy with the production team,

186
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:37,420
so he quit.

187
00:10:37,813 --> 00:10:39,660
I heard you are
still preparing for the film

188
00:10:39,660 --> 00:10:41,013
and haven't started production, yet.

189
00:10:41,060 --> 00:10:42,220
We thought about it

190
00:10:42,568 --> 00:10:44,340
and felt like giving you another chance.

191
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:45,580
After all,

192
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:47,340
you did so many changes
for Yao previously.

193
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:49,820
It's all fate, right?

194
00:10:50,060 --> 00:10:51,820
You're giving us another chance?

195
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:53,980
I think she's reasonable.

196
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:54,980
She's reasonable.

197
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:08,900
Mr. Lu, do you have anything
you want to say?

198
00:11:10,580 --> 00:11:12,820
Mr. Lu wants to go to the toilet.

199
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:13,700
Sorry.

200
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:30,060
You should calm down.

201
00:11:30,060 --> 00:11:31,700
We are preparing for our new film.

202
00:11:31,700 --> 00:11:33,580
No one cares about it on the Internet.

203
00:11:34,420 --> 00:11:35,860
Yes. Shi Huo cooperates well with us,

204
00:11:35,860 --> 00:11:36,820
but no one knows him.

205
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:37,820
No one cares about him.

206
00:11:38,580 --> 00:11:39,940
With Lu Zhiyao here,

207
00:11:39,940 --> 00:11:41,700
he might
bring some attention to the film,

208
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:42,340
right?

209
00:11:42,820 --> 00:11:45,020
Look at how much
he has been teased by others.

210
00:11:45,020 --> 00:11:46,820
Bad publicity is still publicity.

211
00:11:47,060 --> 00:11:48,420
You invested such a huge amount

212
00:11:48,700 --> 00:11:50,420
but what do you have right now?

213
00:11:50,835 --> 00:11:52,380
Isn't it all over if you lose money?

214
00:11:52,380 --> 00:11:53,460
You'll be doomed.

215
00:11:56,060 --> 00:11:56,940
Let me speak.

216
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:01,940
Sorry.

217
00:12:06,340 --> 00:12:07,220
Mr. Lu,

218
00:12:07,302 --> 00:12:09,568
I had a quick discussion
with Director Zhuang just now.

219
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:10,620
We are happy

220
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:12,540
and also hope
you can join our production.

221
00:12:12,540 --> 00:12:13,060
Yes.

222
00:12:13,060 --> 00:12:13,940
However,

223
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:16,260
the actor for the role of the Wizard

224
00:12:16,260 --> 00:12:17,180
has been decided.

225
00:12:17,502 --> 00:12:19,620
It's not right to replace him
for no reason.

226
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:22,380
We have a better role
that's also eye-catching.

227
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,060
It's the role of the Demon King.

228
00:12:24,060 --> 00:12:26,220
I think it suits you a lot.

229
00:12:26,368 --> 00:12:28,140
Do you want Yao
to be a supporting character?

230
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:29,060
That's impossible.

231
00:12:30,820 --> 00:12:31,820
In terms of pay,

232
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:33,340
we can increase it.

233
00:12:33,460 --> 00:12:34,060
Also,

234
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:35,860
his name will be part of

235
00:12:35,860 --> 00:12:37,300
the film's Special Starring.

236
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:38,100
Yes.

237
00:12:47,580 --> 00:12:49,420
Mr. Lu,
do you still need to go to the toilet?

238
00:12:50,391 --> 00:12:52,220
The right hand means
he wants to go to the toilet.

239
00:12:52,220 --> 00:12:53,657
The left hand means he is thinking.

240
00:12:59,591 --> 00:13:02,070
Actually, I don't really care
about the importance of the role.

241
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:05,500
He just wants to be promoted,

242
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,680
so he doesn't care
about the role's importance.

243
00:13:08,820 --> 00:13:10,380
However, this version right now

244
00:13:10,657 --> 00:13:12,980
still lacks depth
when it comes to the characters.

245
00:13:14,220 --> 00:13:16,300
He didn't even read the script.

246
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:18,420
It's all empty talk.

247
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:23,340
When I accept a role,

248
00:13:23,820 --> 00:13:25,980
I will usually find how I resonate

249
00:13:25,980 --> 00:13:27,180
with this character.

250
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:30,060
However, in this version,

251
00:13:30,860 --> 00:13:32,100
I haven't seen

252
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:33,860
the depth of the Demon King's soul.

253
00:13:33,860 --> 00:13:35,780
I also can't feel the role's spotlight.

254
00:13:36,980 --> 00:13:39,820
He just wants me
to give him more scenes.

255
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:45,100
Director Zhuang,
is there a problem with your spine?

256
00:13:45,620 --> 00:13:46,220
All right.

257
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:47,820
Mr. Lu,

258
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:50,740
you can tell us
your specific requirements.

259
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:53,260
The Demon King and the Wizard

260
00:13:53,524 --> 00:13:55,060
should understand each other well,

261
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:57,000
right?

262
00:13:57,770 --> 00:13:58,440
Yes.

263
00:13:59,220 --> 00:14:00,260
Fundamentally speaking,

264
00:14:00,660 --> 00:14:03,060
the Demon King and the Wizard
are not enemies but rivals.

265
00:14:03,060 --> 00:14:04,020
They are equal

266
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:05,220
and are on par with each other.

267
00:14:06,180 --> 00:14:06,820
Right?

268
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:13,060
So, you can just make them

269
00:14:15,420 --> 00:14:16,540
into two male leads.

270
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:24,540
You can stay here and think about it.

271
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:26,260
I have to go to the toilet.

272
00:14:34,180 --> 00:14:35,420
It was cold last night.

273
00:14:35,420 --> 00:14:37,420
I can't hold it in
since I'm getting old.

274
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:43,260
His digestive system is bad.

275
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:46,420
Double male leads?

276
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:49,860
The Wizard has too many scenes.

277
